children.subject: Ruby on Rails preferred, but not required.
Just checking that this is a virtual position right?

history.content:
Resumewabi is hiring a fullstack developer!
I'm a 2nd-year masters student at Cal, and I started resumewabi.com 3 months ago. We use machine learning to provide users with recommendations that improve their resumes and increase the likelihood of landing interviews. We've done significant customer research to validate the idea and our MVP is complete. We began building our beta 2 weeks ago, which we plan to launch by September. I'm planning on working on this full time after graduation. 
Team: We're looking for 1 fullstack developer, who can work with us over the summer (and potentially into the fall). We understand you may already have commitments over the summer and are happy to discuss flexible part-time options.
We have a team of 1 data scientist, 1 backend engineer and 1 fullstack developer. We're building our product using rails. We also have team members working on marketing and product. Our advisors include the co-founder of the Android podcast Fragmented (who is also a Senior Staff Engineer at Instacart) and an ex-Apple Design Evangelist. 
If you'd like to work with us (or just talk about the options), email me at namrata_mani@berkeley.edu.
